The paper discusses the use of deep generative models for anomaly detection in imbalanced datasets, which is a common problem in many data analysis applications, including medical image analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of GANs and VAEs, which are popular deep learning models, indicating a possible fit for cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
